you back from me all this time.

1219
01:25:55,892 --> 01:25:58,217
- Thank you.
- You're welcome. Come on.

1220
01:26:06,279 --> 01:26:07,358
Oh, man.

1221
01:26:13,245 --> 01:26:16,697
Handle your business, baby. Handle it.

1222
01:26:21,046 --> 01:26:22,920
Shelby, I have something...

1223
01:26:23,007 --> 01:26:27,254
Julian, before you say anything, I just
want you to know that I forgive you.

1224
01:26:27,553 --> 01:26:29,048
- You do?
- Yes.

1225
01:26:29,138 --> 01:26:34,181
I know now that you were just succumbing
to that testosterone peer pressure.

1226
01:26:35,104 --> 01:26:39,149
You wanted to be with me last night
and it ate you up that you couldn't.

1227
01:26:39,442 --> 01:26:42,527
It just made sense that
you should continue to suffer...

1228
01:26:42,613 --> 01:26:45,947
and think about the jeopardy
you put our relationship through...

1229
01:26:46,033 --> 01:26:47,860
rather than let you have your way.

1230
01:26:47,951 --> 01:26:49,612
- I have...
- We're out of time.

1231
01:26:49,704 --> 01:26:51,993
I'm sure it can wait
until the reception.

1232
01:26:52,082 --> 01:26:53,789
You better get inside.

1233
01:26:57,964 --> 01:27:00,881
Candace! I'm so glad you could make it.

1234
01:27:01,760 --> 01:27:04,168
You look great.

1235
01:27:09,893 --> 01:27:11,637
Candace, this is Shelby.

1236
01:27:12,188 --> 01:27:13,813
Shelby, Candace.

1237
01:27:13,899 --> 01:27:16,473
It's nice to meet you.
How are you doing?

1238
01:27:16,693 --> 01:27:17,938
I'm so sure.

1239
01:27:19,989 --> 01:27:21,982
So, shall I just sit anywhere?

1240
01:27:22,408 --> 01:27:23,784
Sure, yeah.

1241
01:27:24,077 --> 01:27:27,363
Okay. Thanks, Julian.

1242
01:27:28,123 --> 01:27:29,534
No, thank you.

1243
01:27:33,838 --> 01:27:36,590
Who was that pop tart?

1244
01:27:38,927 --> 01:27:41,881
Shelby, it's over.

1245
01:27:42,682 --> 01:27:45,599
I am not the man for you.
And you are not the woman for me.

1246
01:27:45,685 --> 01:27:47,974
So let's just stop fooling ourselves.

1247
01:27:48,063 --> 01:27:52,227
I hope you find what you're looking for,
because that's what I plan to do.

1248
01:27:54,403 --> 01:27:57,025
I have to go. 'Bye, Shelby.

1249
01:28:03,873 --> 01:28:05,996
Don't you think you oughta pick that up?

1250
01:28:06,084 --> 01:28:07,162
What?

1251
01:28:07,502 --> 01:28:08,913
Your bottom jaw.

1252
01:28:09,880 --> 01:28:12,501
Q. 'Morning, Shelby.

1253
01:28:12,799 --> 01:28:15,884
- Go to hell!
- I'll probably see you there.

1254
01:28:18,013 --> 01:28:19,556
Where's Lance?

1255
01:28:19,683 --> 01:28:22,173
I was just gonna ask you the same thing.

1256
01:28:23,061 --> 01:28:26,348
- I'm sorry. Robin, Quentin.
- How you doin'?

1257
01:28:26,607 --> 01:28:27,686
Hi.

1258
01:28:29,109 --> 01:28:32,028
- Hi. You must be Robin.
- Hi. My pleasure.

1259
01:28:32,197 --> 01:28:33,442
This is Murch.

1260
01:28:33,656 --> 01:28:36,326
- This idiot don't know where Lance is.
- What?

1261
01:28:37,495 --> 01:28:40,449
That's not good. Not good at all.
What are we gonna do?

1262
01:28:40,540 --> 01:28:41,619
- I don't know.
- Something?

1263
01:28:41,707 --> 01:28:42,823
You're not helping.

1264
01:28:42,918 --> 01:28:46,287
- You need to figure something out.
- I'm under stress here.

1265
01:28:49,174 --> 01:28:51,582
It's your fault that all this happened.

1266
01:28:53,096 --> 01:28:54,839
What have you been doin'?

1267
01:28:55,974 --> 01:28:58,596
Lance. Lance! Hey!

1268
01:28:59,436 --> 01:29:03,102
I told you the wedding is off.
I came to tell my parents that I'm out.

1269
01:29:03,191 --> 01:29:06,525
- You ain't doin' that.
- That bullshit ain't working today.

1270
01:29:07,279 --> 01:29:10,399
- Lance, brother. This isn't...
- Why are you even here?

1271
01:29:11,617 --> 01:29:13,575
You got nothing to say to me.

1272
01:29:14,579 --> 01:29:15,777
Yo, L.

1273
01:29:21,211 --> 01:29:23,205
He wouldn't even look at me.

1274
01:29:23,630 --> 01:29:27,760
- Yeah, but you have to make him!
- How am I gonna make him?

1275
01:29:27,844 --> 01:29:31,130
I don't know. Divine intervention.
I don't know!

1276
01:29:31,306 --> 01:29:33,383
Just get in there. Be creative.

1277
01:29:35,102 --> 01:29:38,638
- Divine intervention.
- Hey, you can do this.

1278
01:29:39,775 --> 01:29:41,234
You have to.

1279
01:29:42,319 --> 01:29:43,350
Go.

1280
01:29:50,954 --> 01:29:55,451
Don't do this. You don't wanna do this.
You just need to breathe, relax.

1281
01:29:55,709 --> 01:29:58,082
- Lance, hold on, man.
- Will you hold up?

1282
01:29:58,171 --> 01:29:59,749
Please don't do this.

1283
01:30:03,218 --> 01:30:05,591
Mama, Daddy, I got something
I gotta tell you.

1284
01:30:05,679 --> 01:30:09,464
Wait! Lance, wait.
I gotta tell you somethin'.

1285
01:30:12,228 --> 01:30:14,387
Lance! Pray!

1286
01:30:14,898 --> 01:30:16,310
Wait for a second.

1287
01:30:18,777 --> 01:30:20,107
What'd you say?

1288
01:30:22,031 --> 01:30:23,656
Pray. Pray.

1289
01:30:24,576 --> 01:30:26,984
You want me to beat you
down again, man?

1290
01:30:37,257 --> 01:30:38,835
Pray with me, brother.

1291
01:30:40,303 --> 01:30:42,378
What? What?

1292
01:30:44,515 --> 01:30:47,054
What is it? What is it?

1293
01:30:49,313 --> 01:30:50,938
I should've worn my diamonds.

1294
01:30:51,023 --> 01:30:53,941
No, the pearls are perfect.
You look beautiful.

1295
01:30:54,069 --> 01:30:56,690
- Lord, did I order the right food?
- Yes.

1296
01:30:56,905 --> 01:30:58,814
Something's gonna go wrong.

1297
01:31:00,868 --> 01:31:01,899
Hi.

1298
01:31:06,958 --> 01:31:08,239
Hi, Mia.

1299
01:31:11,130 --> 01:31:14,748
I'm Robin, Harper's girlfriend.

1300
01:31:15,093 --> 01:31:18,378
Oh, Robin, yes! Hi!

1301
01:31:19,305 --> 01:31:23,600
- How are you, my sister?
- I'm fine, but are you all right?

1302
01:31:23,727 --> 01:31:26,053
Because you really look beautiful.

1303
01:31:26,897 --> 01:31:29,139
Thank you. I'm fine.

1304
01:31:32,362 --> 01:31:33,560
I got jitters.

1305
01:31:34,573 --> 01:31:37,575
I mean, I know it sounds silly...

1306
01:31:38,285 --> 01:31:40,445
but if this day isn't perfect...

1307
01:31:41,456 --> 01:31:42,619
Mia!

1308
01:31:43,834 --> 01:31:46,503
Honey, I have something
that I need to tell you.

1309
01:31:46,587 --> 01:31:50,253
And I think that you might want
to sit down for this.

1310
01:31:50,550 --> 01:31:51,665
What is it?

1311
01:31:51,760 --> 01:31:55,674
Sometimes I'm really nosy
and I let my job consume me...

1312
01:31:55,848 --> 01:31:57,887
and I don't think sometimes.

1313
01:31:58,016 --> 01:32:01,516
And I know that this whole thing
is probably really my fault.

1314
01:32:01,812 --> 01:32:03,640
Baby, you are scaring me.

1315
01:32:05,108 --> 01:32:06,686
Right. It's Lance.

1316
01:32:07,194 --> 01:32:10,314
- The thing is...
- He's running late.

1317
01:32:11,866 --> 01:32:14,440
- I'm Robin. Nice to meet you.
- Hi.

1318
01:32:15,537 --> 01:32:17,115
- Running late?
- Great.

1319
01:32:17,206 --> 01:32:22,710
Yeah. That's what I came in here
to tell you. He's running a little late.

1320
01:32:23,838 --> 01:32:26,044
But he's here now. Right, Kendall?

1321
01:32:27,092 --> 01:32:28,503
I mean, Jordan.

1322
01:32:30,054 --> 01:32:32,212
He's here. We're just
trying to make sure...

1323
01:32:32,306 --> 01:32:35,758
And he knows how important
this day is for you.

1324
01:32:36,311 --> 01:32:38,583
Harper told me about last night.
They got

1325
01:32:38,584 --> 01:32:40,854
a little wild at the bachelor party.

1326
01:32:41,191 --> 01:32:43,861
Girl, please, spare me the details.

1327
01:32:43,945 --> 01:32:45,967
I'm sure they were on
their best behavior.

1328
01:32:45,968 --> 01:32:47,989
I'm sure of it.

1329
01:32:51,162 --> 01:32:54,116
So we just have a little C.P.
Time for now.

1330
01:32:54,540 --> 01:32:55,999
Yeah. C.P.

1331
01:32:57,169 --> 01:32:58,200
Okay.

1332
01:32:59,921 --> 01:33:01,713
But they'll wait for you.

1333
01:33:01,924 --> 01:33:05,792
Yeah, they'll wait for me. It's my day.

1334
01:33:06,262 --> 01:33:08,053
It's all good.

1335
01:33:14,271 --> 01:33:15,896
What scripture, man?

1336
01:33:16,690 --> 01:33:18,683
How about Exodus 20:14?

1337
01:33:19,276 --> 01:33:21,519
Exodus 20:14. Cool.

1338
01:33:25,242 --> 01:33:26,701
"Thou shalt not..."

1339
01:33:32,918 --> 01:33:35,076
"Thou shalt not commit adultery."

1340
01:33:35,296 --> 01:33:37,288
- Damn.
- What's he readin'?

1341
01:33:38,132 --> 01:33:42,130
Look, man, I'm just trying to stop you
from making a big mistake.

1342
01:33:42,220 --> 01:33:45,969
- By running up in my woman?
- Is that what you want to hear?

1343
01:33:46,058 --> 01:33:48,763
- I wanna hear the truth.
- You don't want the...

1344
01:33:51,480 --> 01:33:55,479
All you want to hear is that
you're an amazing running back...

1345
01:33:56,153 --> 01:33:58,193
and that your wife-to-be is perfect.

1346
01:33:58,280 --> 01:34:00,653
When the truth is, you
could actually use

1347
01:34:00,654 --> 01:34:03,026
some work on your lateral moves and...

1348
01:34:03,912 --> 01:34:05,572
your short yardage.

1349
01:34:06,539 --> 01:34:09,209
And a long, long time ago...

1350
01:34:11,170 --> 01:34:13,247
Mia slept with your best man.

1351
01:34:17,010 --> 01:34:21,174
I could've killed you last night.
You know that? I still could right now.

1352
01:34:22,141 --> 01:34:25,676
You could, man,
but it wouldn't change anything.

1353
01:34:27,814 --> 01:34:31,231
I made a terrible, terrible mistake.

1354
01:34:33,070 --> 01:34:34,529
And I'm sorry, man.

1355
01:34:36,699 --> 01:34:39,321
- I would give you my right arm...
- Fuck that.

1356
01:34:46,252 --> 01:34:49,206
You said yesterday
that you would forgive her.

1357
01:34:49,297 --> 01:34:52,749
- So you calling me a hypocrite?
- You're not being realistic.

1358
01:34:53,344 --> 01:34:56,215
This isn't the Bible.
This is the real world.

1359
01:34:56,555 --> 01:35:00,803
And Mia is as close to perfection
as you're gonna get.

1360
01:35:01,019 --> 01:35:04,851
I guess you got all the answers.
Everything is so fucking logical to you.

1361
01:35:04,940 --> 01:35:06,518
Come on. You're in a church.

1362
01:35:06,609 --> 01:35:09,943
The answers are fucked wherever you are!
You can't control me.

1363
01:35:10,029 --> 01:35:14,110
I'm not one of your little characters
in one of your little stories, man!

1364
01:35:14,451 --> 01:35:18,449
You can't control this outcome.
You know why? Because you are not God.

1365
01:35:19,498 --> 01:35:22,535
- That's reality, motherfucker!
- Listen to reason.

1366
01:35:37,937 --> 01:35:39,311
I knew.

1367
01:35:41,815 --> 01:35:45,979
I always knew in the back of my mind
that she had been with somebody else.

1368
01:35:46,196 --> 01:35:49,067
But never in a million lifetimes
would I think...

1369
01:35:50,325 --> 01:35:54,075
that you was gonna be that
self-serving, back-stabbing bastard.

1370
01:36:01,046 --> 01:36:02,790
You can hate me forever.

1371
01:36:04,634 --> 01:36:06,009
But not Mia.

1372
01:36:07,428 --> 01:36:09,885
She loves you so much.

1373
01:36:12,852 --> 01:36:15,972
Man, you're staring your ideal woman
in the face.

1374
01:36:21,070 --> 01:36:23,228
You two were made for each other.

1375
01:36:26,910 --> 01:36:28,451
You two fit together.

1376
01:36:32,499 --> 01:36:33,993
She's my Earth.

1377
01:36:36,211 --> 01:36:37,457
She's my queen.

1378
01:36:39,632 --> 01:36:40,878
I know.

1379
01:36:58,863 --> 01:37:00,737
Okay, I'm gonna go get your tux.

1380
01:37:00,823 --> 01:37:02,104
Wait a minute.

1381
01:37:03,410 --> 01:37:05,659
I'm a Christian so I
have to forgive you,

1382
01:37:05,660 --> 01:37:07,907
but that doesn't mean
I have to like it.

1383
01:37:08,749 --> 01:37:09,781
Okay.

1384
01:37:10,251 --> 01:37:13,252
You better find a way to deal
with your issues, too.

1385
01:37:13,337 --> 01:37:15,586
Writing is not gonna
purge you completely,

1386
01:37:15,587 --> 01:37:17,835
so I suggest that you acknowledge Him.

1387
01:37:19,387 --> 01:37:20,418
Him who?

1388
01:37:24,768 --> 01:37:26,178
Okay.

1389
01:37:30,608 --> 01:37:33,692
I feel you, but if I don't get you
into this tux...

1390
01:37:37,241 --> 01:37:39,992
You said you'd get me over that broom.
Remember?

1391
01:37:40,077 --> 01:37:42,366
- I remember.
- Then don't back out on me.

1392
01:37:42,455 --> 01:37:45,207
You recognize His strength.
You respect it.

1393
01:37:47,919 --> 01:37:50,292
Recognize. Respect.

1394
01:37:50,964 --> 01:37:52,044
Okay.

1395
01:39:45,805 --> 01:39:50,800
"Dearly beloved, we are gathered
here today in the sight of God...

1396
01:39:51,686 --> 01:39:55,436
"...to join this man and this woman
in holy matrimony."

1397
01:39:57,985 --> 01:40:00,442
The couple have written
their own wedding vows...

1398
01:40:00,530 --> 01:40:03,531
that they'll speak to each other,
and in front of you...

1399
01:40:03,617 --> 01:40:05,740
their family and dear friends.

1400
01:40:09,457 --> 01:40:10,620
Mia?

1401
01:40:18,091 --> 01:40:20,464
"Lance, my friend...

1402
01:40:22,264 --> 01:40:24,470
"...my love, my hero...

1403
01:40:29,146 --> 01:40:31,139
"...loving you is my heart's joy.

1404
01:40:32,400 --> 01:40:35,900
"It teaches me to be faithful
to my personal truths.

1405
01:40:38,407 --> 01:40:40,614
"As I stand beside you this day...

1406
01:40:41,369 --> 01:40:43,943
"...I offer you the very heart of me...

1407
01:40:45,874 --> 01:40:48,543
"...filled with sacred love...

1408
01:40:49,252 --> 01:40:53,500
"...pure, unconditional and everlasting.

1409
01:40:54,717 --> 01:40:56,876
"For love bears all things...

1410
01:40:57,554 --> 01:41:01,386
"...endures all things
and believes all things.

1411
01:41:01,976 --> 01:41:03,684
"Love never fails.

1412
01:41:05,063 --> 01:41:06,972
"And I do love you, Lance...

1413
01:41:08,608 --> 01:41:10,518
"...mind, body and soul."

1414
01:41:22,415 --> 01:41:23,411
"Mia...

1415
01:41:24,418 --> 01:41:26,957
"...my darling, my love...

1416
01:41:29,132 --> 01:41:31,290
"...as I stand beside you this day...

1417
01:41:32,094 --> 01:41:34,965
"...know that there is nothing greater
than love.

1418
01:41:35,806 --> 01:41:37,431
"For God is love.

1419
01:41:39,810 --> 01:41:42,100
"And having faith in you...

1420
01:41:44,983 --> 01:41:46,940
"...and belief in our love...

1421
01:41:49,780 --> 01:41:51,690
"...makes life worth living.

1422
01:41:52,909 --> 01:41:54,452
"And as I stare...

1423
01:42:02,545 --> 01:42:06,591
"As I stare upon your angelic face...

1424
01:42:11,263 --> 01:42:15,392
"...I am made whole today,
a man with a higher purpose.

1425
01:42:16,186 --> 01:42:19,804
"For a woman's virtue
is a man's greatest glory.

1426
01:42:22,318 --> 01:42:24,026
"From this day forth...

1427
01:42:24,695 --> 01:42:28,564
"...we should love one another
as God loves us."

1428
01:42:32,997 --> 01:42:34,540
The rings, please.

1429
01:42:38,920 --> 01:42:42,455
"By the power vested in me,
I now pronounce you...

1430
01:42:42,925 --> 01:42:44,633
"...husband and wife."

1431
01:42:46,345 --> 01:42:48,173
Please, kiss your bride.

1432
01:43:49,668 --> 01:43:52,338
Mia gave me too much credit
for this union.

1433
01:43:53,839 --> 01:43:55,916
I have learned from them...

1434
01:43:57,678 --> 01:44:01,546
what it means to be truly committed
to another person.

1435
01:44:03,017 --> 01:44:05,639
I have learned the importance...

1436
01:44:06,604 --> 01:44:08,348
of seizing the moment.

1437
01:44:09,775 --> 01:44:11,602
Because you can't go back.

1438
01:44:13,321 --> 01:44:16,192
You can never go back.
You have to live for today.

1439
01:44:17,533 --> 01:44:22,529
Not for what was, or could have been.

1440
01:44:25,043 --> 01:44:26,537
And what will be...

1441
01:44:28,546 --> 01:44:30,255
no one can say.

1442
01:44:34,928 --> 01:44:36,258
But sometimes...

1443
01:44:40,101 --> 01:44:42,509
you just have to step out on faith.

1444
01:44:45,357 --> 01:44:46,935
And believe that...

1445
01:44:47,360 --> 01:44:51,488
what you have built together
is worth preserving.

1446
01:44:55,870 --> 01:44:58,954
Because when you're made
for each other as much...

1447
01:45:01,125 --> 01:45:02,834
as these two are...

1448
01:45:06,757 --> 01:45:08,335
it's definitely...

1449
01:45:09,677 --> 01:45:11,717
definitely worth preserving.

1450
01:45:22,234 --> 01:45:24,060
So, to the bride and groom.

1451
01:45:27,364 --> 01:45:28,775
Lance and Mia...

1452
01:45:29,659 --> 01:45:30,987
I love you.

1453
01:45:33,246 --> 01:45:35,998
And may God bless this union.

1454
01:45:40,629 --> 01:45:41,709
Cheers.

1455
01:46:02,321 --> 01:46:03,484
Bravo, baby.

1456
01:46:35,943 --> 01:46:38,648
Okay, ladies, who's ready
to catch the bouquet?

1457
01:46:38,738 --> 01:46:41,312
Single females, on the floor. Let's go.

1458
01:46:41,408 --> 01:46:43,365
Mia, are you ready?

1459
01:46:44,995 --> 01:46:46,656
Okay, here we go.

1460
01:46:52,963 --> 01:46:53,912
Bitch.

1461
01:46:54,172 --> 01:46:55,371
Thanks, Mia.

1462
01:46:58,302 --> 01:47:01,637
- All right. You know what comes next.
- Go get your girl.

1463
01:47:01,722 --> 01:47:03,217
Come on out, y'all.

1464
01:47:03,767 --> 01:47:06,055
- Q, you know you want to.
- What?

1465
01:47:06,144 --> 01:47:09,311
Uncle Skeeter, you don't need
to catch this. Sit your butt down.

1466
01:47:09,398 --> 01:47:12,435
Let's see what happens.
Just throw. You never know.

1467
01:47:16,573 --> 01:47:17,653
I did not!

1468
01:47:25,416 --> 01:47:26,911
I'm gettin' you.

1469
01:48:00,832 --> 01:48:02,078
Cut it out.

1470
01:48:02,168 --> 01:48:04,373
Quit acting like you don't like it.

1471
01:48:08,716 --> 01:48:09,914
You like it.

1472
01:48:13,972 --> 01:48:15,550
Say you like it.

1473
01:48:19,938 --> 01:48:21,266
Say you like it.

1474
01:48:22,858 --> 01:48:24,186
Stop it!

1475
01:48:27,321 --> 01:48:29,231
Don't let her get away, dog.

1476
01:48:35,622 --> 01:48:37,200
- Go get her, Q.
- That's scary.

1477
01:48:39,084 --> 01:48:41,001
I think we have to dance.
Care to dance?

1478
01:48:41,002 --> 01:48:42,917
Yes, I'd love to.

1479
01:48:47,720 --> 01:48:51,255
Quentin better be careful
before Shelby puts a hurtin' on him.

1480
01:48:53,184 --> 01:48:54,216
Yeah.

1481
01:48:57,356 --> 01:48:58,980
Dance with me?

1482
01:49:00,150 --> 01:49:01,395
You know...

1483
01:49:03,071 --> 01:49:05,644
I just want to talk to you.

1484
01:49:15,126 --> 01:49:17,285
Cut a rug with a war vet, darling?

1485
01:49:18,839 --> 01:49:20,796
Sure, Uncle Skeeter.

1486
01:49:21,007 --> 01:49:22,171
Come on.

1487
01:49:28,475 --> 01:49:31,761
It's been a crazy-ass,
emotional weekend, hasn't it?

1488
01:49:32,646 --> 01:49:35,103
Damn roller-coaster ride.

1489
01:49:38,194 --> 01:49:40,864
Listen, about last night, Jordan.

1490
01:49:41,990 --> 01:49:45,740
I don't want to hear about last night.
If I hear you mention last night...

1491
01:49:45,827 --> 01:49:49,577
I'm gonna call the Enquirer
and tell them everything I know.

1492
01:49:49,833 --> 01:49:51,457
So it's like that?

1493
01:49:51,752 --> 01:49:55,833
Okay, I hear you loud and clear,
Miss Armstrong. Thank you.

1494
01:49:56,924 --> 01:49:58,253
You're welcome.

1495
01:50:06,477 --> 01:50:08,803
I saw you grabbin' for that garter.

1496
01:50:13,193 --> 01:50:14,652
You know what?

1497
01:50:15,695 --> 01:50:17,190
I don't blame you.

1498
01:50:18,241 --> 01:50:20,067
She's a beautiful woman.

1499
01:50:20,868 --> 01:50:22,493
She's the one.

1500
01:50:25,541 --> 01:50:27,082
Just don't blow it.

1501
01:50:34,426 --> 01:50:36,134
I love you, Harper.

1502
01:50:50,653 --> 01:50:53,061
Excuse me, Robin,
I don't mean to interrupt...

1503
01:50:53,155 --> 01:50:55,528
but Uncle Skeeter
did promise me a dance.

1504
01:50:55,617 --> 01:50:59,829
Seeing he's the only available man in
the whole wedding party, I was just...

1505
01:50:59,913 --> 01:51:02,749
Come on, baby girl.
You don't mind, do you, darling?

1506
01:51:02,833 --> 01:51:04,458
No, not at all.

1507
01:51:05,962 --> 01:51:09,248
And besides I think the best man
over there needs you.

1508
01:51:17,392 --> 01:51:20,309
Come on, Uncle Skeeter.
Don't be tryin' to touch my booty.

1509
01:51:20,395 --> 01:51:21,558
No, no.

1510
01:51:43,130 --> 01:51:45,538
Thank you for helping me today.

1511
01:51:47,593 --> 01:51:48,874
You're welcome.

1512
01:51:50,555 --> 01:51:51,883
Great speech.

1513
01:51:55,519 --> 01:51:58,189
- I was moved.
- You know I meant every word...

1514
01:51:58,940 --> 01:52:01,811
every word I said about
preserving what we have, and...

1515
01:52:01,901 --> 01:52:04,571
I don't think that this
is the right time.

1516
01:52:06,156 --> 01:52:09,941
We have a lot to talk about
and it's not gonna be solved overnight.

1517
01:52:11,036 --> 01:52:14,536
- We have to figure out some...
- You know what your problem is?

1518
01:52:15,250 --> 01:52:17,326
You don't live enough for today.

1519
01:52:18,628 --> 01:52:19,874
What?

1520
01:52:21,799 --> 01:52:23,958
For once, just live in the moment.

1521
01:52:30,226 --> 01:52:31,886
Harper, what are you doing?

1522
01:52:31,978 --> 01:52:33,887
At least for a little while.

1523
01:52:42,364 --> 01:52:43,444
Robin...

1524
01:52:47,829 --> 01:52:49,407
will you marry me?

1525
01:52:53,544 --> 01:52:55,002
I love you.

1526
01:52:59,717 --> 01:53:00,832
Please.

1527
01:53:05,767 --> 01:53:06,798
Yeah.

1528
01:53:09,312 --> 01:53:10,640
Whatever, man.

1529
01:54:20,018 --> 01:54:22,094
Come and get it goin' on, y'all.

1530
01:54:22,271 --> 01:54:24,560
Five, six, seven, eight.

1531
01:56:14,650 --> 01:56:16,025
Housekeeping.

1532
01:56:26,747 --> 01:56:29,155
- Damn! I shouldn't have drank!
- What did I do?

1533
01:56:29,250 --> 01:56:32,002
I ain't drinkin' no more liquor!

1534
01:56:33,672 --> 01:56:35,380
Did you touch me?